I"p<p>John Conway’s Game of Life is a mathematical demonstration showing how, based on initial conditions, cells can live or die with each passing generation.</p>

<p>The rules are as follows:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Cells with less than two live neighors die.</li>
  <li>Cells with more than three live neighbors die.</li>
  <li>Cells with two or three live neghbors survive to the next generation but are unchanged.</li>
  <li>Dead cells with three live neighbors regenerate.</li>
</ol>

